Chidiebube Okeoma The police in Imo state have apprehended 22 suspected cult members in the state. Parading the suspects, the state Commissioner of Police, Olaniyi Fafowora, said the suspects were arrested at a popular hotel at Orlu on January 24, 2020. He said the suspects confessed that they were hired to disrupt the supplementary election held on January 25 by a yet-to-be identified person. The CP gave the names of the suspects as Ordu Kennedy, Igweuba Chukwudi, Maxwell Junior, Ezeigwe Promise, Kalu Emmanuel, Okoli Obinna, David Onyebuchi, Samuel Uche, Ikenna Nnajimere and Orisakwe Chukwuebuka. Others are Chidiebere Justine, Nduka Chibuzor, Solomon Nkemjika, Nwosu Emmanuel, Nnamdi Onuoha and Uchenna Uchewe, David Dominic, Nwosu Chidozie, Emmanuel Peter, Michael Chimamkpa, Adigwe Ikechukwu and Nduka Chimobi. The police chief disclosed that two-locally made pistols, five live cartridges, one walkie-talkie and six live cartridges were recovered from the suspects. The CP said, “On January 24, upon credible intelligence, operatives of the command stormed a popular hotel at Ihioma, in the Orlu LGA and arrested the suspects alleged to have been brought in by a yet-to-be-identified person to disrupt the supplementary election of January 25 but due to the proactive and intelligence-led policing approach of the command, they were rounded up. “Wraps of dried leaves suspected to be Indian hemp and two cut-to-size locally-made pistols, one walkie-talkie and six live cartridges were recovered. The hotel manager was also arrested for questioning. “Investigation is in progress with a view to identifying and arresting the mastermind of this unlawful act who shall be arraigned with his cohorts.” Copyright PUNCH.
